  "decision_conditions": [
    "The Planning Inspectorate allow the appeal and grant listed building consent for addition of mansard roof extension to match adjacent houses at 99 Cloudesley Road, London, N1 0EN in accordance with the terms of the application (Ref: P040670) dated 18th March 2004 and the plans submitted therewith subject to the following conditions.\r\n\r\n1.  The works hereby permitted shall be begun before the expiration of five years from the date of this consent.\r\n\r\n2.  No works shall take place until samples of materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the extension hereby permitted have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  Works shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.\r\n\r\n3.  Any alterations or making good of the retained fabric of the building shall be undertaken with materials to match those existing.\r\n\r\n4.  No works shall take place until drawings of an appropriate scale showing details of dormer windows and rooflights, including all window joinery details and the relationship of the frames to the openings have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  The works shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.\r\n\r\n5.  No works shall take place until a method statement for works to the plaster cornicing and around the upper windows of the Cloudesley Road elevation have been submitted and approved by the Local Plannig Authority.  The works shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details."
